For 16S rRNA and HLA-C data, the .RData file stores the model input parameters:

Y_obs: chimera matrix

S_matrix: similarity matrix

effective_cycle: effective number of cycles

D: sequencing depth

K: number of species

freq_initial: initial frequency

N: initial number of molecules



For DMS (Deep Mutational Scanning) data, the model inputs are provided as separate text files (parameters.txt), consisting of:

Y_obs_rep1.txt — Observed chimera matrix for replicate 1

Y_obs_rep2.txt — Observed chimera matrix for replicate 2

S_matrix.txt — Similarity matrix

freq_obs_rep1.txt — Observed frequency data for replicate 1

freq_obs_rep2.txt — Observed frequency data for replicate 2

output_results.txt — Output results file

effective_cycle — Effective number of amplification cycles

D_rep1 — Sequencing depth for replicate 1

D_rep2 — Sequencing depth for replicate 2

K — Number of species (variants)
